HEADWORD: Subhornblendic
<hw>Sub`horn*blend"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Containing hornblende in a scattered state; of or relating to rocks
containing disseminated hornblende.</def>⟦br⟧
